# GoalPulse Enterprise Hardening — Implementation Plan

## Overview

Full-stack audit of the AtomQuest / GoalKeeper codebase has been completed. The system is architecturally sound (React 18 + TypeScript + Vite + TailwindCSS + Node.js/Express + Supabase), but several critical gaps exist between the current prototype state and a production-grade, hackathon-winning enterprise SaaS. This plan addresses them in priority order.

---

## Critical Findings from Audit

| Area | Issue | Severity |
|---|---|---|
| **Team Goals — Backend** | `GET /:teamId/goals` only fetches goals tagged with `team_id`. There is no dedicated endpoint to **create** a team-scoped goal. The existing `POST /api/goals` allows a `team_id` but has no enforcement that the caller is a team member. Team goals don't work end-to-end. | 🔴 Critical |
| **Team Goals — Frontend** | `TeamDetail.tsx` Goals tab lists goals from the API but has zero UI to **create**, **edit**, or **delete** a team goal. The tab is entirely read-only. | 🔴 Critical |
| **Admin `/completion` N+1** | `GET /api/admin/completion` runs nested `await` calls for every employee inside a `Promise.all`, causing N+1 sub-queries. 50 employees = 150+ Supabase round-trips per request. | 🔴 Critical |
| **Missing route — Team Goals POST** | No `POST /api/teams/:teamId/goals` endpoint exists at all. | 🔴 Critical |
| **Seed script reliability** | Seeder creates users but doesn't guarantee team + goal linkages, so the demo can start in a broken state with empty Team Goals tab. | 🟡 High |
| **Security — Input Validation** | `POST /api/goals`, `POST /api/teams`, auth routes accept raw body values with no length guards or sanitization. XSS/injection risk via `title`, `description`, `name`. | 🟡 High |
| **Rate Limiting — AI endpoints** | `/api/ai/*` has zero rate limiting. A user could exhaust the Groq quota mid-demo. | 🟡 High |
| **AppLayout sidebar nav bug** | "Manager Teams" nav item is visible to EMPLOYEE role — it shouldn't be. | 🟡 High |
| **Performance — `enrichTeams`** | Makes 3 sequential Supabase queries (teams → members → goals → achievements). Should be parallelized. | 🟠 Medium |
| **UX — Empty states** | Team Goals tab shows nothing meaningful when empty. Reports and Analytics pages show raw spinners with no skeleton loaders. | 🟠 Medium |

