## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Team Goal Ownership Model**: Should employees create their own team-scoped goals (current plan — self-assign via `team_id`), or should the manager push goals down to employees? The current architecture supports the self-assign model with no DB changes. The push model needs an `assigned_by` column and different RBAC logic.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **AI Rate Limit for Demo**: 20 req/15 min on `/api/ai/*` is production-safe but potentially too low for a live judge demo with multiple concurrent users. Recommend 50 req/15 min for the hackathon environment.

> [!NOTE]
> **GoalWizard reuse for team goals**: The existing `GoalWizard` component already supports a `team_id` prop path through `POST /api/goals`. We can reuse it in TeamDetail by passing `teamId` and calling the new `POST /api/teams/:teamId/goals` endpoint, OR keep it calling `POST /api/goals` with `team_id` in the body. The latter requires less frontend change.
